# Catppuccin Theme – Latte (Light) / Mocha (Dark)

Primary accent: **Teal**

## Tailwind Color Utilities

Use these Tailwind classes directly — they auto-switch between Latte and Mocha:

### Palette colors
`bg-rosewater`, `text-flamingo`, `border-pink`, `bg-mauve`, `text-red`,
`bg-maroon`, `text-peach`, `bg-yellow`, `text-green`, `bg-teal`,
`text-sky`, `bg-sapphire`, `text-blue`, `bg-lavender`

### UI layers (background → foreground)
`bg-crust` → `bg-mantle` → `bg-base` → `bg-surface0` → `bg-surface1` → `bg-surface2`

### Typography
- Body / headings: `text-foreground` or `text-text`
- Subtitles, labels: `text-subtext1`, `text-subtext0`
- Muted / subtle: `text-muted` or `text-overlay1`
- Text on accent backgrounds: `text-on-primary`

### Semantic aliases
- Primary: `bg-primary`, `text-primary` (maps to teal)
- Background: `bg-background` (maps to base)
- Foreground: `text-foreground` (maps to text)
- Borders: `border-border` (maps to surface0)
- Focus ring: `ring-ring` (maps to lavender)
- Status: `text-success`, `text-warning`, `text-destructive`, `text-info`

## Rules
- NEVER use hardcoded hex colors — always use Catppuccin token classes
- NEVER use Tailwind `dark:` variant — theme switching is handled via CSS variables
- Use `bg-surface0` or `bg-surface1` for cards, inputs, and interactive surfaces
- Use `border-surface1` for borders between elements
- Opacity modifiers work: `bg-teal/20`, `text-overlay2/50`
